1
00:00:06,407 --> 00:00:08,778
Here's a list of colors and materials.
这是一张颜色和材料的清单.

2
00:00:09,219 --> 00:00:10,496
If you ever want to match something,
如果你要配点什么,

3
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:11,525
take the list to the store.
可以带这张单子去店里买.

4
00:00:11,670 --> 00:00:12,370
Thanks.
谢谢.

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,208
And here's your final invoice.
这是你最后的发票.

6
00:00:15,236 --> 00:00:19,292
Fine. I can write a check now, if that's OK.
好的.我现在就可以开支票,如果没问题的话.

7
00:00:19,541 --> 00:00:22,871
Bill, you're my favorite client.
Bill,你是我最喜欢的顾客.

8
00:00:23,007 --> 00:00:25,477
I just wish I had more than two rooms for you to do.
我真希望我有超过两个房间可以请你们装潢.

9
00:00:25,654 --> 00:00:28,272
Just call us when you have a house, OK?
等你有了大房子就给我们打电话,好吗?

10
00:00:28,505 --> 00:00:30,814
I'm sure all your clients come back.
我相信你们所有的客户都会成为回头客.

11
00:00:31,968 --> 00:00:33,413
All but one.
只有一个不是.

12
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:38,356
Oh, really? You have to tell me.
Oh,真的?这你得跟我讲讲.

13
00:00:38,755 --> 00:00:39,914
I'm your favorite client.
我可是你们最喜欢的顾客.

14
00:00:40,937 --> 00:00:42,983
He had no sense of color.
他对色彩没有一点感觉.

15
00:00:44,859 --> 00:00:49,942
One day last summer, we got a call.
去年夏季的一天,我们接到个电话.

16
00:00:50,722 --> 00:00:55,971
It was a doctor, a very successful surgeon
是一位医生,一位非常成功的外科医生

17
00:00:56,116 --> 00:00:59,417
who wanted us to design his consulting offices.
他想请我们设计他的诊室.

18
00:00:59,604 --> 00:01:02,218
And it was very important to the big surgeon...
对那位名医来说,有一点非常重要

19
00:01:02,489 --> 00:01:03,493
Nan...
Nan...

20
00:01:03,740 --> 00:01:06,008
...that the colors be soothing.
色彩要让人感到平和、放松.

21
00:01:06,306 --> 00:01:08,110
Well, that makes sense.
Well,有道理.

22
00:01:08,341 --> 00:01:10,089
I had no problem with that.
对此我毫无异议.

23
00:01:10,314 --> 00:01:18,606
However, the surgeon and my partner could not agree on green.
但是,那位外科医生与我的合伙人在绿色的问题上意见不一致.

24
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:22,222
Green is...green, right?
绿色就是绿色，对不对?

25
00:01:22,437 --> 00:01:25,756
It was a very soft sea foam green, 
是种非常柔和的海水泡沫般的绿色,

26
00:01:26,011 --> 00:01:28,292
very gentle on the eyes.
有非常柔和的视觉效果.

27
00:01:28,533 --> 00:01:29,850
What color is that?
那是什么颜色?

28
00:01:30,065 --> 00:01:31,035
Green.
绿色.

29
00:01:31,221 --> 00:01:32,236
Thank you.
谢谢.

30
00:01:32,417 --> 00:01:37,950
Well, the surgeon said the green was yellowy-brown 
Well,那位外科医生把那种绿色说成是黄褐色,

31
00:01:38,145 --> 00:01:39,981
and not relaxing at all.
而且根本无法让人放松.

32
00:01:40,177 --> 00:01:43,750
In fact, he said the green was...
事实上,他说那种绿色是...

33
00:01:44,568 --> 00:01:45,411
what did he call it?
他怎么说来着?

34
00:01:45,576 --> 00:01:49,389
Institutional. Do you believe it? 
单调俗套的.你相信吗?

35
00:01:49,597 --> 00:01:52,070
He gave me such a headache.
他让我如此头痛.

36
00:01:52,237 --> 00:01:56,691
Green, yellow, green, yellow. 
绿色,黄色,绿色,黄色.

37
00:01:57,282 --> 00:02:00,635
We finally went with a shade of pink...
最后我们用了一种粉色...

38
00:02:00,776 --> 00:02:02,147
Which he called violet.
他说那是紫色.

39
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:05,387
And the man is an eye surgeon!
这人居然是个眼外科医生!

